    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-11-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-12-28T20:20:13Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Civilian Service Recognition Act of 2006 - Requires executive agencies to furnish a U.S. flag to drape the casket of a civilian federal employee who dies in a combat zone, upon request of the deceased's next of kin or a close associate of the deceased. </p> <p>Requires notification of federal civilian employees who are located or stationed in a combat zone to perform one or more functions in support of military operations of the flag ceremony benefit provided for under this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
